name: TIME FACE ZOoM
description: by Markus Oehlen - While the titles serve as ironic analogies and contextual references they also hint towards pandemic demands for new forms of representation of artworks and artists through online studio visits, zoom meetings or face time conversations. His used materials partially date back to the 1970s, from which Oehlen transforms various drawings through intense photo-copying into something characterized by distortion, warping and twisting that is then contextually supported by sound.
